remarks: Any nonempty bounded subset of integers has a supremum in the set.  (The proof does not use ~ ax-pre-sup .)  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 21-Apr-2015.)
statement:
zsupss $p |- ( ( A C_ ZZ /\ A =/= (/) /\ E. x e. ZZ A. y e. A y <_ x ) -> E. x e. A ( A. y e. A -. x < y /\ A. y e. B ( y < x -> E. z e. A y < z ) ) ) $.
$d A x y z $.
$d B x $.
$d x y $.
